  <abstract>A simple log cabin is depicted. According to the text, the home is The Hermitage of Andrew Jackson, built in 1804. The print was inspired by an image from the collection of the Ladies' Hermitage Association in Nashville, Tennessee.</abstract>
  <abstract>The Jacksons occupied this simple log cabin in 1804. Later, a mansion was constructed; they expanded their property and eventually developed a 1,100-acre plantation that was home to about 150 slaves.</abstract>
